{
  "title": [
    "cusp~"
  ],
  "description": "cusp map chaotic generator",
  "origin": "ELSE",
  "categories": [
    "Random and Noise",
    "Signal Generators"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "frequency in Hz (negative values accepted)"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "description": "3 floats sets 'a', 'b' and y[n-1]"
        },
        {
          "type": "set <float, float>",
          "description": "<channel, freq> set a single frequency channel"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "cusp map chaotic signal"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "sets frequency in Hz",
      "default": "Nyquist"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "sets 'a'",
      "default": "1"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "sets 'b'",
      "default": "0.19"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "sets initial value of y[n-1]",
      "default": "0"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [
    {
      "name": "-mc <list>",
      "description": "sets multichannel output with a list of frequencies"
    }
  ],
  "methods": [],
  "body": "[cusp~] is a chaotic generator using the difference equation;\ny[n] = a - b * sqrt(abs(y[n-1]))\nThe output rate of the equation is given in Hz (default: Nyquist).\nObject based on SuperCollider's \"CuspN\" UGEN."
}